content.detailedDescription: I was living in oregon at the time and my house was secluded in a densly wooded area about 5 minutes out of town. i was staying up late playing my xbox. it was around 3 o clock a.M. when suddenly my house lost all electricity. at that time, my house and every room in it including rooms with  closed doors became very brightly lit.  so bright i could barely see my hands in front of me. i heard my mom yell very loudly " what the hell is going on". i was still sitting on my couch next to a window covered by curtains. out of curiosity i moved the curtains back to take a look outside. i remember very clearly seeing a very brightly lit disk-shaped object hovering about 30 - 50 feet above my house. it looked metallic and had 5-10 white lights around the edges. they did not pulse.  it also had 1 red light in the middle on the bottom of the craft that pulsed emanating a bright glow resembling a flare. when it continued its path it moved in a zig-zag formation at a slightly higher elevation above the tree-tops. it traveled at a very fast speed stopping for a second everytime it traveled in a straight line and then changing direction. i saw it move for about 5 times in a zig zag formation before it sped off in one straight direction at a very high speed and it was gone in the blink of an eye. the most strange and most important and memorable detail of the craft to me personally, was the fact that it left odd tracers as it moved. it was as if it disapeared and reapeared in another spot in the sky leaving tracers that followed it slowly and as soon as the tracers cought up with the craft the craft began moving again. this type of craft and the way it moved eerily reminded me of a supposed nasa file that was captured by a orbiting satelight. in this file the very similar-looking craft came from earth at a very high speed and hovered a few feet next to the satelight and then taking off into space and leaving the strange "tracers" as it came from earth and as it took off into space.  i do not know if the file was real or hoax but seemed legit to me. real or not though the craft in the file i am refering to seemed almost identical to the craft i saw that early morning in oregon. also one last detail, about 5-10 minutes after i saw this craft, a black helicopter or at least looked black in the night sky, flew over our house at a good speed very low over our house and traveled in the direction i saw the ufo travel to. helicopters are not seen commonly in the town i lived in. especially not low flying helicopters and especially not at 3 in the morning so i found this very odd as well.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Disk shaped,brightly lit

content.detailedDescription: Sitting on the sofa looking out the window there was a bright fog type area. it was supposedly the time of solar flares, and then walking over to the window i saw this orb that was a blue/green very very bright behind the trees. i yelled at my wife to come see. she freaked out and told me to get a camera and get pics. she wanted to try to get closer to it. she jumped in the car with the video camera but the trees are thick and she went down the hill which she should have driven up the hill. she said she pulled the car over to take a picture but the light was so bright it was like after you have a camera flash. she could not see well for about an hour. her eyes were very blurry. she took a picture but only got the bright white light. she could not get in a position to take a picture of the blue. i got one but it was long distant. i wish i could blow it up somehow. maybe i will go to walmart and see if we can blow up the picture. it was really unnerving. after she went close to it she felt nausea and couldnt see well.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home........ and i looked up and saw a massive "v" shaped object hovering out side of the city....... there were 6 bright white on the bottom.  3 on each side of "v".  it was a dark color black or drak grey......  i saw for at least 30 seconds it may have there longer..... as i was watching there wasnt any noise, just light traffic....... then is just vanished......  after that i was still driveing  and looking and i could see planes  where the object was..I counted at least 10 or more  planes and they were what looked like searching. when i got home the planes where still there and were there for like an hour ..... i wish i was not driving so i could filmed it and taken pictures...... but hands down the coolest thing i have seen..... i always did believe  in that stuff..... but not now i am 100% positive....
content.summary: V shaped object hover out side of  city

content.detailedDescription: On monday january 23, 2012 while heading home to fayetteville from farmington, arkansas, i noticed a bright star like light in the sw sky. the time was about 8:15 p.M. more or less. initially the light was about 30-40 degrees above the horizon. i first noticed it when i turned on hamestring rd. where i stopped my car completely, rolled down my window and watched it. it looked stationary and appeared to be about the height most aircraft. i kept driving and stopped not far down the road and rolled down my window again to view the light. it looked as if it might have been traveling horizontally very slowly. however, it was hard to tell if it was because there was an airplane flying in its vicinity and that may have given me the impression that it was moving. the light was very bright and resembled a planes landing light, but was more star like. in fact when i first saw it i thought that it was a plane but i was wondering why it wasnt moving. i have seen airplanes and helicopters with their landing lights on so i know how they can appear starlike, especially if they facing you and are heading in your direction. i continued driving on to john garrison rd. all the while keeping the light in my sight. when i pulled into our driveway, the light was still in my sight in the sw. i took a couple of bags inside and grabbed my binoculars (i didnt get my camera because at this point i thought it was probably something ordinary) to better view the object. i went back outside immediately and stood by the field next to my house to study this light. between when i first noticed the light while i was driving and when i arrived in my yard with my binoculars about five minutes had passed. for what seemed like 10 minutes i watched this light, which appeared to hover or remain in the same spot in the sky, and considered the possibility of it being venus or some other planet. for at that time i ruled out the possibility of it being aircraft because an aircraft could not stay in the sky in one spot for that long and i could hear no noise coming from this light. the next explanation that made the most sense would be a planet. this light looked similar to venus at its brightest but with obvious differences. it was similar in that it was in the same spot where venus usually is,it appeared to twinkle (it would dim and brighten slightly) and it seemed to be still. it was different in that it was more intensely bright seemed to be larger, and was a yellow-orange color, while venus is more white. after about 10 minutes of observing this light, i ruled out the possibility of it being a planet. it started to move slowly and strangely. it would randomly move in a contained space around itself in various directions. it barely moved from where it had originally been hovering. at first i thought that i might have been mistaken about its movements but i saw it repeat these strange movements over a period of about 5-10 min. this is when i thought "what planet or craft does that?" sometimes the light would move in said manner and sometimes it would remain stationary. throughout the time i was watching the light, it was gradually moving toward the west. it was only apparent that it was moving because the longer i watched it the farther away it got. you could not tell it was moving away unless you studied it for a few minutes. i watched it until it was almost over the horizon. i then headed inside because you could hardly see it anymore. the farther away it got the dimmer it became and it began to take on a reddish tint. throughout the sighting i would look at the light through my binoculars and it just looked like a yellow-orange dot, not quite round like a circle in shape. while this light was in the sky , i could hear dogs barking in the direction of the object. as it got lower in the sky and farther west, the dogs barking quietened but i could still hear the dogs farther to the west barking. the whole time i was watching the light i kept thinking "what is that?" and when it began to move unusually, i thought, " thats incredible!". i kept running through explanations in my head for this light but i couldnt come up with any that didnt have flaws. i have never seen any light move, behave or look like this one. does venus move across the sky in that short amount of time. what else could move the way this light moved? there was a lot of air traffic in the vicinity of the light (including airplanes and jets) for the duration of the sighting. the light didnt really seem to react to these. i was very curious and excited during the sighting. the entire sighting from the time i first saw the light to when it was barely visible on the horizon lasted approximately half an hour, from around 8:15 p.M to 8:45 p.M. i did not attempt to record the light on video or take photographs mainly because i didnt want to go inside and miss this light doing something out of the ordinary. furthermore, it wouldnt have shown up very good in photographs and had i taken a video it probably would have been shaky as there was nothing to rest the camera on. this sighting leaves me with a lot of questions. i cannot come up with an explanation. i am surprised that there arent more reports from the area on this light. im sure that other people saw it as well.
content.summary: Starlike light hovered and moved strangely then gradually traveled to the horizon

Was at work having cigarette. noticed bluish light hovering around level of cloud cover. watched it for around thirty seconds, then it took off in a northern direction.

oddly, though i don't know if it's related or not, the weather got much rougher after it had left, and the area experienced winds of up to 60kmph afterwards.

content.detailedDescription:
travelling late at night westbound on us 50 ten or so miles east of eureka, nv near junction with highway 379.  

     it was dark but i could see the mountian range directly ahead.  to the right of the road was a set of red and blue lights with the blue light about 5 feet of the ground, the red light was about 20 feet directly above it.  the two lights began to spin on a vertical plane about a horizontal axis.  from my vantage point in the car the two lights became a circle of lights about 20 -30 feet in diameter.

the lights then just disapeared.  

     then seconds later from behind me and came directly over my car at a high altitude was a streak of light (like a shooting star). the light went over the mountian ahead of me. from over the ridgeline light radiated out at the summit in rays of silver-gold glittery lights.  about 5-6 rays and it looked like the crown of the statue of liberty.  within seconds it was all over.

please do not contact me
content.summary: Us 50 nevada lights become circle then become streak of light and then a flareout

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend and i were roadtripping from los angeles to florida, taking the i10 east for the majority of the trip.

at approximately 7:24am, about 50 miles east of el paso, i observe a bright white light to the north of i10. the sun had been up for about an hour and at first i assume the light i am seeing is a star or the sun's reflection on an aircraft.

after maybe 7-10 seconds of me looking at the light, it blinks out, leaving an empty blue sky. i look away from the northern horizon for about 3 seconds (long enough to see that my girlfriend is sound asleep in the passenger seat) before looking back to see another bright white light, this one much further east but at roughly the same altitude and intensity as the first light.

i stare again for maybe 8 seconds before the light begins to fade in a circular motion, from the bottom upward - as if the light were rotating around the object - from a bright white to a dullish silver, to a dark grey, to a faint egg-on-its-side silhouette before completely vanishing again. this entire process lasted 3-4 seconds at most.

for the next several minutes, i search the skies in vain as the lights do not make a reappearance.

i also noted two nearby jet streams, one almost directly under the first light (from my perspective), and a second much further to the east of both sightings.

aside from the jet streams, the sky was as clear as could be. i will not even attempt to estimate the distance we were from the lights, but they appeared to be at the approximate height you would expect to see a commercial aircraft, and about the size and intensity of a bright star.

after about 5 minutes of trying to process what i'd just witnessed, i text my father an entire blow-by-blow of the experience. my girlfriend wakes up about 10 minutes after the sighting and immediately comments that i appear shaken up; after telling her the story, she is upset that i did not wake her up during the sighting. i tell her that the entire event lasted 20-30 seconds at most and that i did not know (and still don't) what i was witnessing until after it had happened.

we watched the skies carefully for the rest of the morning. this region of texas along i10 is fairly desolate and we did not see any other aircraft for several hours after the event.

while i am a little disappointed that my first ufo sighting can only best be described as a "bright white light," i am truly dumbfounded as to what i saw in the northern skies over west texas that morning.
content.summary: Observed starlike-light that vanished, then reappeared, then faded to an egglike shape before disappearing again

content.detailedDescription: Was going to see captain amercia at movie when at 9.00 pm looked up and saw 4 in diamond formation follow parallel to railroad tracks. as lights passed me they turned and started to head away from me.As this occured light went out and you could see faint out line of an object behind light. as first four passed second group of 5 came by in loose formation.Followed by several more with a last light at 9.05 which seemed to be a straggler and was late trying to catch up with group. all followed same path. at first i thought they were ultra lights however i did not hear any sound, which was un-nerving. i live close to a small airport so i am used to aircraft sounds. i was not only person to witness lights four other people did also. on sunday a state police chopper was seen following same path.I worked in aero-space field they have me stumped!!!!!!
content.summary: 15-20 yellow red  orbs in diamond formation

content.detailedDescription: I was flying to my sisters in atlanta, georgia for thanksgiving dec 19th 2011. as we were half way into the flight, aprox 11am to 12 noon, i looked out the window and observed a cigar shaped object that was aprox 5 to 8 miles away & seemed to be aprox 3 to 4 football fields long, silver outer shaped along with darker features inside of the shape. i rubbed my eyes, kept seeing it for 5 seconds, then i turned to the man sitting next to me and said "look, do you see that"? he looked out and said no! as i looked back out, it was gone!I was jut relaxing at the time, just looking out the window from time to time,it was so large, that's why i noticed it. i know when i saw it it was not of this world as i was in the u.S. navy & worked on aircraft & worked for the dod and government contractors! it was stationary didn't seem to move. i was excited! and nervous!Lost sight when i turned to the man in the seat next to me. i really hope someone else reported the same type of object on the same day, time, and location. please direct me where to go to find out that info, thank you!
content.summary: I flew to atlanta airport from los angeles, aprox half way there i looked out the window & observed a cigar shaped object

content.detailedDescription:
This past saturday morning approx 2am i went to let my dog out in the backyard. she did her business but ran to the other side of the house. i called her and she didn't come so i toll approx 8-10 steps toward the rear of the house and my attention was drawn to a light just above the trees in my backyard. i looked up at this light thinking it was a police light but as i kept looking there was no other light except this blue. very strange light almost bright and dull if that makes sense. i watched this ball of light which was only above the trees and in clear view for what i would say was five
minutes. not one movement or sound from the object the blue light was steady and there were yellow lights in it shining through the blue. the only thing the light did was sort of flash which scared me terribly and i ran back inside the house. i crept over to my window to look from my bedroom and the ball of light was gone. i have been overcome with fear since and i haven't slept during darkness since. i have also woken up suddenly in the days since with no explanation of how i got there. i cannot understand any of this and i am terribly frightened of what i stumbled upon. i must stress i was never threatened by the light and it never interacted with me however i believe that i interrupted whatever it was doing. i have contacted multiple people to try and figure out what happened with no luck as of yet.
content.summary: Outside my house above tree in backyard there was a ball of light. no structure looked like energy. very close to me

content.detailedDescription:
2 nights in a row, both nights at appx 6:45pm cst, moving much faster than any jet i've seen, going appx from sw to ne, saw a glowing, slowly pulsating white light.
no other lights normally seen on a jet or plane.  pulsated every 4 to 5 seconds, going from bright to dim to bright again.  not on and off.
no sound
straight path until out of sight.  slightly different flight path 2nd night from 1st.
my 28yr old son witnessed the 2nd sighting and verified these details.

i am regular star gazer, have seen some anomolies, but nothing like this.
content.summary: Fast moving, slowly pulsating white light

content.detailedDescription: I had walked out on to my front stoop to smoke a cigarette & heard a strange noise not unlike a jet engine but whirring instead of that linear scream. then the object came into view from behind, in-between my home & the two story home to the right(there was never any question of what it was); it looked like a black disk with a silver seven pointed pentagram on the domed/bubbled bottom with several randomly appearing rectangle red lights & one bar shaped light at the end of each point outlining  the circle. i was instantly very happy, kind hearted, sexually aroused to a flash erection, loving & appreciative of life(not my usual but has not left yet) the object continued across the street, over the high school drive-way then did a 1/4 circle curve out of my sight behind a very small hill. i felt like my dog died for a split second, saw a white strobe for about four flashes from the other side of the hill & have felt a bit high on life with a touch of horney anxiety. for a few days now & a reaccuring thought that a 'reunion' is approaching. it only seemed to take..Maybe 30 seconds but my cig. had burned away & out completely. unfortunately i was much too passive and "love drunk" to think of looking at the time again but it seemed a good deal quieter & i felt amazing like that "oh thank 'god' it's the perfect gift right on time let's f**k to celebrate" feeling if that makes sence?  i was silent for a-while, finally told my friend today & he said "report it" so here.
content.summary: Walked out front to smoke passed me @45° angle from back 30yrds off ground felt calm & grateful

content.detailedDescription: Was inside on my laptop my wife had gone outside to have a cigarette and she had come back inside all excited saying something was in the sky.I dont know what the object is i have seen it two separate occasions in the summer time as well the object resembles a star but much to low on the horizon much brighter than the rest it stayed in one spot for about 10 minutes then slowly faded out same as previous two sightings
content.summary: Spotted in the sky remained in one spot whole 10 minutes then faded out

content.detailedDescription: Sitting in living room, i saw this very large flaming ball outside through trees which then went up at a 30 degree angle, so i went out front to observe, then through back door to continue to watch its path.  it angled sharply upward then, all the time looking like it was afire, and finally, after maybe 3-5 minutes, disappeared when it was very high in the sky.  it was traveling in a northeast direction.  we have a lot of plane traffic  but it was definitely not an aircraft.  my first reaction was that it looked like a hot air balloon burning.
content.summary: Flaming
